tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE QuantumHardwarePredictions (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    hardware_name VARCHAR(255),
    quantum_model VARCHAR(255),
    historical_data JSON,
    prediction_result JSON
);

CREATE TABLE historical_data (
  entry_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  hardware_id INT,
  performance_metric VARCHAR(100),
  measurement_value FLOAT,
  measurement_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE future_trends (
  trend_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  trend_description VARCHAR(255),
  hardware_model VARCHAR(100),
  predicted_performance FLOAT,
  prediction_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE historical_data (
    data_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    hardware_id INT,
    observation_date DATE,
    temperature FLOAT,
    voltage FLOAT,
    CONSTRAINT fk_hardware FOREIGN KEY (hardware_id) REFERENCES quantum_hardware_data(hardware_id)
);

CREATE TABLE trends_analysis (
    trend_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    data_id INT,
    trend_description TEXT,
    trend_score INT,
    CONSTRAINT fk_data FOREIGN KEY (data_id) REFERENCES historical_data(data_id)
);

CREATE TABLE future_predictions (
    prediction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    trend_id INT,
    prediction_date DATE,
    predicted_performance FLOAT,
    CONSTRAINT fk_trend FOREIGN KEY (trend_id) REFERENCES trends_analysis(trend_id)
);

CREATE TABLE performance_metrics (
    metrics_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    hardware_id INT,
    metric_date DATE,
    metric_name VARCHAR(100),
    metric_value FLOAT,
    CONSTRAINT fk_hardware_metrics FOREIGN KEY (hardware_id) REFERENCES quantum_hardware_data(hardware_id)
);
